clonePlace(25.10)                                            clonePlace(25.10)

Name
       clonePlace - Places all clone instances with relative location and rel-
       ative orientation according to the master partition instances

Syntax
        clonePlace

       [-help]

       [-clone_list <cloneinstance(s)orientation(s)>]

       [-master_inst <instance name>]

       Places all clone instances with relative location and relative orienta-
       tion according to the master partition instances. Adjusts instance ori-
       entation based on the clone orientation. Use this command after running
       place_design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each clonePlace.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man clonePlace

       -clone_list<cloneinstance(s)orientation>
              Specifies clone instances with relative location.

       -master_inst <instance name>
              Specifies the master partition instance.

Related Information
              * place_design

